
==Setup Your Repository==

The main foursquared repo is at http://joelapenna.com/git/foursquared.git

*Some files must be manually created in order for the tests and source to build.*

*Create main/res/values/credentials.xml* -- do not check this in. It must contain strings:

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<resources>
  <string
    name="google_maps_api_key">SOME_TEST_KEY</string>

  <string
    name="oauth_consumer_key">SOME_OTHER_KEY</string>
  <string
    name="oauth_consumer_secret">SOME_OTHER_OTHER_KEY</string>


  <!-- A stanza like this will be sufficient if you're not testing dumpcatcher capabilities. ->
  <string
    name="dumpcatcher_url"></string>
  <string
    name="dumpcatcher_product_key"></string>
  <string
    name="dumpcatcher_secret"></string>

  <!-- A stanza like this will be sufficient if you're not testing dumpcatcher capabilities. ->
  <string
    name="test_dumpcatcher_url"></string>
  <string
    name="test_dumpcatcher_product_key"></string>
  <string
    name="test_dumpcatcher_secret"></string>


</resources>

*Create tests/src/com/joelapenna/foursquare/TestConstants.java* -- do not check this in. It must contain strings:

public class TestConstants {

    static final String oAuthConsumerKey = "SOME_OTHER_KEY";
    static final String oAuthConsumerSecret = "SOME_OTHER_OTHER_KEY";

    static final String testFoursquareUsername = "testuser@example.com";
    static final String testFoursquarePassword = "some_password";

	public static final String testFoursquarePhone = "";
	public static final String testFoursquarePassword = "";

}


==Ideas==

+ "Lead" a Bar Crawl
Use your phone to generate a "proxy" authentication credentials and store that on your client. Pass that authentication credential onto another phone, maybe by QRCode and allow others to act on your behalf. Provide UI on your phone to disable that credential by sending an RPC to /api/logout with those credentials.

This will give a user the ability to designate someone else as their notifier. This allows people to form up for a bar crawl, with one person leading the checkins for foursquare.

+ Shortcuts to favorite checkins.

+ Yelp Integration


-------------
URL for location suggestion provider.
curl 'http://playfoursquare.com/venues?q=pie&cityid=23'

+ CHECKIN Example
http://m.playfoursquare.com/checkin?privacy=0&security_token=&shout=&twitter=0&venue=Noc+Noc

-- Request Headers
Host: m.playfoursquare.com
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; U; Linux i686; en-US; rv:1.9.0.8) Gecko/2009032711 Ubuntu/8.10 (intrepid) Firefox/3.0.8
Accept: text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,*/*;q=0.8
Accept-Language: en-us,en;q=0.5
Accept-Encoding: gzip,deflate
Accept-Charset: ISO-8859-1,utf-8;q=0.7,*;q=0.7
Keep-Alive: 300
Connection: keep-alive
Referer: http://m.playfoursquare.com/checkin
Cookie: SESSIONID=bcf5bd566449ba0a2be9d7dc8bf02cb4; cookieCityID=23

-- Response Headers
Date: Sun, 05 Apr 2009 16:10:05 GMT
Server: Apache
Expires: Thu, 19 Nov 1981 08:52:00 GMT
Cache-Control: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, post-check=0, pre-check=0
Pragma: no-cache
Content-Length: 2809
